 } } \right]$$<br><br>A has inverse, if $$\left| A \right| \ne 0$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| A \right| = 1\{ (x - 1)(x - 3) - 7\}  - 3(x - 3 - 2) + 2\{ 7 - 2(x - 1)\}  \ne 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {x^2} - 11x + 29 \ne 0$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$x \ne {{11\, \pm \sqrt {121 - 116} } \over 2}$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x \ne {{11 \pm \sqrt 5 } \over 2}$$
